Now that we have the taxable income, let us compute the income tax expense.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Income tax expense}&=\text{Taxable income}\times\text{Tax rate}
\\[10pt]
&= \$393,000\times21\%\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{{\$82,530}}
\end{aligned}$$

As shown in the above computation, Griffin's Goat Farm, Inc. has an income tax expense of $82,530.
